# Proxy Service (WebFlux)

Applies under `proxy/` (adjust `globs` in this file if the proxy module path changes).

## Reactive runtime

1. Use reactive return types (`Mono` / `Flux`) for proxy and streaming flows where appropriate.
2. Do not block reactive event-loop threads.
3. If using blocking APIs (for example `RabbitTemplate`), offload to a dedicated scheduler (see architecture doc §6.2).
4. Do not force a single synchronous response wrapper on streaming or SSE-style endpoints.

## Provider relay

1. Treat upstream provider calls as I/O-bound; use non-blocking clients (`WebClient`) and appropriate timeouts.
2. Preserve streaming semantics when the client expects chunked or SSE responses.

## Context

- Proxy is the only WebFlux-first service; other backends may use Spring MVC + JPA under `services/`.
